      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VINTAGE GEM (2) made an impressive debut when charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, scoring an all the way win (22.72) over 400m at this track. Promising type and can make it two on the bounce. UNHOOKED (1) collided with another runner and finished a well held 5 lengths fourth (23.19) last time in a Novice race at this track over 400m. Rates a leading chance on best. MAKO EIFFLER (8) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at this track over 300m behind Just A Favour (17.85) in a Novice race. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Has the ability to give this a shake. REIKO BOOM (7) dominated last start. Big chance on that form.",
